<style>
    body {
        background-color: #edd2b7;
    }

    .card-error {
        max-width: 380px;
        margin: auto;
        margin-top: 10vh;
        background-color: #fff;
        padding: 30px;
        border-radius: 12px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        text-align: center;
    }

        .card-error i {
            font-size: 3rem;
            color: #dc3545;
        }

        .card-error h4 {
            margin-top: 15px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .card-error p {
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #555;
        }

        .card-error .btn {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
</style>

<div class="card-error">
    @*<i class="bi bi-house-door"></i>*@
    <img src="../Content/Images/Alumni-DigitalId-logo.png" style="height: 100px" />

    <h4>Welcome</h4>
    <p style="text-align: justify; text-justify: inter-word;">
        A Digital ID is a secure, digital representation of a person's identity that can be used for online authentication and access to services, both public and private. It's a way to prove who you are electronically, streamlining various processes and reducing reliance on physical documents. Digital IDs can store various forms of identity information, including biographical data, biometrics, and other relevant attributes, often using encryption and secure storage methods.
    </p>
    <a href="@Url.Action("Login", "Account")" class="btn btn-danger w-100">Login</a>




